# Force LF line endings on checkout, regardless of platform git config.
#
# Without this, Git for Windows' default core.autocrlf=true (set in its
# system gitconfig by the installer) silently rewrites every file with
# CRLF endings on checkout / fetch / refresh. GitHub Desktop uses bundled
# Git for Windows and inherits the same default. The resulting CRLF files
# break shell-script execution under WSL and produce phantom "all 32
# files modified" diffs that have no content delta — only line-ending drift.
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` means: auto-detect text vs binary, but for text
# files always check out as LF. Vendored gcc-3.0 source is upstream-LF
# throughout; build.sh / install.sh / configure scripts all need LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Treat binaries unambiguously (skip any text-like processing).
*.gz binary
*.bz2 binary
*.tar binary
*.zip binary
*.bin binary
*.o binary
